{
    "question_text": "<h3>Subarray Product Less Than K</h3><p>Given an array of integers <code>nums</code> and an integer <code>k</code>, return the number of contiguous subarrays where the product of all the elements in the subarray is <b>strictly less than</b> <code>k</code>.</p>",
    "difficulty": "MEDIUM",
    "marks": 10,
    "input_format": "First line: space-separated integers representing array `nums`. Second line: integer `k`.",
    "output_format": "A single integer representing the count of valid subarrays.",
    "constraints": [
        "1 <= nums.length <= 3 * 10^4",
        "1 <= nums[i] <= 1000",
        "0 <= k <= 10^6"
    ],
    "explanation": "We use a sliding window. We maintain a running product and two pointers `left` and `right`. As we expand `right`, we multiply the product by `nums[right]`. While the product >= k, we divide by `nums[left]` and advance `left`. At each valid position, the number of new subarrays ending at `right` is `right - left + 1`. If k <= 1, no positive product can be strictly less than k, so we return 0. This runs in O(N) time and O(1) space.",
    "answer": "def solve(nums, k):\n    if k <= 1: return 0\n    prod = 1\n    left = count = 0\n    for right in range(len(nums)):\n        prod *= nums[right]\n        while prod >= k:\n            prod //= nums[left]\n            left += 1\n        count += right - left + 1\n    return count",
    "boilerplate": {
        "python": "import sys\n\ndef solve(arr, k):\n    return 0\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    lines = sys.stdin.read().splitlines()\n    if len(lines) >= 2:\n        arr = list(map(int, lines[0].strip().split()))\n        k = int(lines[1].strip())\n        print(solve(arr, k))",
        "cpp": "#include <iostream>\n#include <vector>\n#include <sstream>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint solve(vector<int>& arr, int k) {\n    return 0;\n}\n\nint main() {\n    string line;\n    if (getline(cin, line)) {\n        vector<int> arr;\n        stringstream ss(line);\n        int val, k;\n        while (ss >> val) arr.push_back(val);\n        if (cin >> k) cout << solve(arr, k) << endl;\n    }\n    return 0;\n}",
        "java": "import java.util.*;\npublic class Main {\n    public static int solve(int[] arr, int k) { return 0; }\n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);\n        if (sc.hasNextLine()) {\n            String[] parts = sc.nextLine().trim().split(\"\\\\s+\");\n            if (parts.length == 0 || parts[0].isEmpty()) return;\n            int[] arr = new int[parts.length];\n            for (int i = 0; i < parts.length; i++) arr[i] = Integer.parseInt(parts[i]);\n            if (sc.hasNextInt()) System.out.println(solve(arr, sc.nextInt()));\n        }\n    }\n}",
        "javascript": "const fs = require('fs');\nfunction solve(arr, k) { return 0; }\nconst input = fs.readFileSync(0, 'utf8').trim().split('\\n');\nif (input.length >= 2) {\n    const arr = input[0].trim().split(/\\s+/).map(Number);\n    console.log(solve(arr, parseInt(input[1])));\n}",
        "c": "#include <stdio.h>\n#include <stdlib.h>\nint solve(int* arr, int n, int k) { return 0; }\nint main() {\n    int capacity = 1000;\n    int* arr = (int*)malloc(capacity * sizeof(int));\n    int n = 0, k;\n    char c;\n    while (scanf(\"%d\", &arr[n]) == 1) {\n        n++;\n        if (n == capacity) { capacity *= 2; arr = (int*)realloc(arr, capacity * sizeof(int)); }\n        c = getchar();\n        if (c == '\\n' || c == EOF) break;\n    }\n    if (scanf(\"%d\", &k) == 1) printf(\"%d\\n\", solve(arr, n, k));\n    free(arr);\n    return 0;\n}"
    },
